# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project by following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File Modified:** `package.json`, `package-lock.json`
- **Action:** Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- **Version:** Latest version added to dependencies

### 2. Analytics Integration
- **File Modified:** `frontend/src/App.jsx`
- **Changes:**
  1. Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
  2. Added `<Analytics />` component inside the main App component, placed within the `<AuthProvider>` wrapper to ensure analytics are tracked across the entire application

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was strategically placed at the root level of the application (within the BrowserRouter and AuthProvider context) to ensure:
- All page views and navigation events are tracked
- Analytics work across all routes (Home, Upload, Download, SignIn, Register)
- The component is initialized once and persists throughout the user session

## Framework-Specific Configuration

Following the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite applications:
- Used `@vercel/analytics/react` import (framework-specific)
- Added the `<Analytics />` component to the root App component
- No additional configuration or setup files required

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter passed for modified file (`eslint src/App.jsx`)
✅ No new errors or warnings introduced
✅ Application structure and existing functionality preserved
✅ All dependencies updated and lock file generated

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views once the application is deployed to Vercel
- No environment variables or additional configuration needed
- Analytics data will be visible in the Vercel dashboard after deployment
- The implementation follows React best practices and integrates seamlessly with the existing React Router setup

## Next Steps for User

1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. Visit your deployed application to generate analytics data
4. Check the Vercel dashboard to view analytics insights
